                            <comment id="17096477" author="rtrivedi12" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2020 12:28:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;During doAuthorization() call for CreateDatabase operation , authorize is invoked only with read and write&#160;Privileges for the operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void authorize(Privilege[] readRequiredPriv, Privilege[] writeRequiredPriv)
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; HiveException, AuthorizationException {
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In StorageBasedAuth, we only call checkPermissions() for root warehouse dir (hive.metastore.warehouse.dir) and not the specified location. So, any user who does not have access to directory will be able to create database if they have access to warehouse path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Path root = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
  initWh();
  root = wh.getWhRoot();
  authorize(root, readRequiredPriv, writeRequiredPriv);&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
