                            <comment id="17104347" author="shubhamchaurasia" created="Mon, 11 May 2020 11:15:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the pointers &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rtrivedi12&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rtrivedi12&quot;&gt;rtrivedi12&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mgergely&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mgergely&quot;&gt;mgergely&lt;/a&gt;. Based on our discussion, I agree that it would be cleaner to have an API with authorizer inputs and outputs rather than passing the properties in HiveConf as the current patch does. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For context, currently we are having below API in &lt;tt&gt;HiveAuthorizationProvider&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void authorize(Privilege[] readRequiredPriv,
      Privilege[] writeRequiredPriv) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; HiveException,
      AuthorizationException;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now in &lt;tt&gt;StorageBasedAuthorizationProvider&lt;/tt&gt; we need some additional information, in this case the custom location of database from &apos;CREATE DATABASE&apos; query. Current patch achieves this by passing the location via HiveConf. To be able to pass inputs and outputs explicitly we would need something like below - &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void authorize(Privilege[] readRequiredPriv,
      Privilege[] writeRequiredPriv, Set&amp;lt;ReadEntity&amp;gt; inputs, Set&amp;lt;WriteEntity&amp;gt; outputs) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; HiveException,
      AuthorizationException;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But since &lt;tt&gt;HiveAuthorizationProvider&lt;/tt&gt; is a public/pluggable interface, I am not sure about modifying it. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hashutosh&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hashutosh&quot;&gt;hashutosh&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thejas&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thejas&quot;&gt;thejas&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mgergely&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mgergely&quot;&gt;mgergely&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Does the above API look correct ? How to we usually modify authorizer APIs (or any public API) in hive ? Do we have a doc/guideline for this ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17104351" author="mgergely" created="Mon, 11 May 2020 11:22:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As per our discussion with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ShubhamChaurasia&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ShubhamChaurasia&quot;&gt;ShubhamChaurasia&lt;/a&gt;, I also believe that this is the right solution. We have to document it properly that the API has changed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17106945" author="thejas" created="Thu, 14 May 2020 06:13:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, its fine to change this API. It is not widely used outside of Hive AFAIK.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ranger and others use a different HiveAuthorizer interface.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17107149" author="mgergely" created="Thu, 14 May 2020 09:44:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thejas&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thejas&quot;&gt;thejas&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ShubhamChaurasia&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ShubhamChaurasia&quot;&gt;ShubhamChaurasia&lt;/a&gt;&#160;I&apos;d also suggest to find more meaningful names for the methods here. Currently all the functions declared in this interface are called &quot;authorize&quot;, and they differ only in their signature. The aforementioned&#160; function is for (according to it&apos;s comment): &quot;Authorization user level privileges.&quot;. Actually it is called only for create database commands, so we might as well rename it to something like authorizeCreateDatabase. The rest of the methods should be reviewed as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is not closely related to this jira, but as we&apos;ll change the API now anyway, we could do this now too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17168663" author="shubhamchaurasia" created="Fri, 31 Jul 2020 11:54:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review and commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mgergely&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mgergely&quot;&gt;mgergely&lt;/a&gt;. Closing it. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note - It changes API in &lt;tt&gt;HiveAuthorizationProvider&lt;/tt&gt; from &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void authorize(Privilege[] readRequiredPriv, Privilege[] writeRequiredPriv) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; HiveException,      AuthorizationException;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
void authorizeDbLevelOperations(Privilege[] readRequiredPriv, Privilege[] writeRequiredPriv, Collection&amp;lt;ReadEntity&amp;gt; inputs, Collection&amp;lt;WriteEntity&amp;gt; outputs) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; HiveException, AuthorizationException;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
